Add a technology specific frequency band to ViCom.
@note This function handles technology specific frequency bands by supplying a band number. Refer to AddCustomFrequencyBand() to create custom frequency bands where start and stop frequency values are used.
@par Setting the technology value to Technology::CDMA implies CDMA2000, which includes 1xRTT, 1X Advanced, and 1xEV-DO. FastACD will search for both CDMA and EVDO channels in the band(s) requested; however, CDMA and EVDO channel detections will be reported to ViCom as separate results.
@par When the technology is set to Technology::GSM, use the table below to set the band number as there is no standard numerical value assigned to the bands in the 3GPP specification for GSM. The values follow the Roman numerals as shown in section 2 Frequency bands and channel arrangement of the specification. Refer to TS 45.005 version 15.1.0 Release 15 for further information. GSM bands using dynamic ARFCNs are not supported as indicated in the band list below.
@verbatim GSM 380 1 (Unsupported) GSM 410 2 (Unsupported) GSM 450 3 GSM 480 4 GSM 710 5 (Unsupported) GSM 750 6 (Unsupported) GSM 810 7 (Unsupported) GSM 850 8 P-GSM 900 9 E-GSM 900 10 R-GSM 900 11 DCS 1800 13 PCS 1900 14 ER-GSM 900 15 @endverbatim
@param[in] technology An indicator used to assign the band to a specific technology, this avoids overlap with with technologies that have similar bands.
@param[in] band A band number associated with the technology specified.

